@mkouba @Ladicek this seems to be caused by [this](https://github.com/quarkusio/quarkus/blob/cc6b08d6818deb440189dc3ee8bfd3752386a71f/extensions/arc/deployment/src/main/java/io/quarkus/arc/deployment/staticmethods/InterceptedStaticMethodsProcessor.java#L458-L460) code not properly copying over the annotations.

I have prepared a simpler [reproducer](https://github.com/user-attachments/files/16782475/code-with-quarkus.zip) which contains only what is necessary to reproduce the problem (and no Kotlin :)).

You'll see that for something like:

```java
public class Example {

    @Dummy
    public static void doSomething(@NotNull String in1, @NotNull String in2) {

    }
}
```

The `InterceptedStaticMethodsProcessor` results in producing:

```java
public class Example {
   @Dummy
   public static void doSomething_orig(@NotNull String in1, @NotNull String in2) {
   }

   @Dummy
   @NotNull
   @NotNull
   @NotNull
   @NotNull
   public static void doSomething(String var0, String var1) {
      Example_InterceptorInitializer._8f4c528947d72f7f32e813c99a3a20797d8b132f(var0, var1);
   }
}
```
